Class StateManager

java.lang.Object
board.StateManager
public class StateManager
extends java.lang.Object

    • actOnClick

      public void actOnClick​(int clickX, int clickY)
      Receives coordenates, identifies the squares that was clicked on and paints the aquarium up to the square level. If it is already painted, unpaints the aquarium down to the square level. Also updates depth.
      Parameters:
      clickX - x coordinate.
      clickY - y coordinate.

    • reset

      public void reset()
      Unpaints every level on the current state.

      Changes the problem shown.
      Parameters:
      board - board string.
      hc - horizontal numbers.
      vc - vertical numbers.

    • solve

      public void solve()
      Initiates solver thread to reach the solution.

    • giveHint

      public void giveHint()
      Compares the current state to the solution given by the solver thread. Checks if there are any levels that shouldn't painted and unpaints them. If none of those are found it paints a level that should be, starting from the lower ones. Only does one change per call.

    • getLeftSquares

      public void getLeftSquares​(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> h, java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> v)
      Updates 2 lists with the number of squares left to paint, horizontally and vertically.
